+# clonellm LGE Builder Integration
+
+This folder contains the Open WebUI-side integration assets for the local `clonellm` builder service.
+
+`clonellm` must be running first:
+
+```bash
+cd /mnt/c/Users/LLM/Desktop/project/rull/clonellm-openwebui
+PORT=3100 OPENWEBUI_BUILDER_SERVICE_TOKEN=dev-openwebui-builder-token npm run dev:web
+```
+
+## Option A: Import Native Action Function
+
+Import this file in Open WebUI:
+
+```text
+integrations/clonellm-lge-builder/lge_builder_action.py
+```
+
+UI path:
+
+```text
+Admin Panel -> Functions -> Create/Import
+```
+
+Set Valves:
+
+```text
+builder_base_url=http://localhost:3100
+builder_public_url=http://localhost:3100
+builder_service_token=dev-openwebui-builder-token
+default_project_id=lge-openwebui-project
+default_page_id=home
+default_viewport_profile=pc
+```
+
+If Open WebUI runs in Docker while `clonellm` runs on the host, use:
+
+```text
+builder_base_url=http://host.docker.internal:3100
+builder_public_url=http://localhost:3100
+```
+
+## Option B: API Install Function
+
+If Open WebUI is running and you have an admin bearer token:
+
+```bash
+OPENWEBUI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080 \
+OPENWEBUI_ADMIN_TOKEN=<admin-token> \
+python3 integrations/clonellm-lge-builder/install_function.py
+```
+
+The script calls:
+
+```text
+POST /api/v1/functions/create
+```
+
+## Option C: OpenAPI Tool Server Spec
+
+Use this spec if configuring Open WebUI's external OpenAPI tool server support:
+
+```text
+integrations/clonellm-lge-builder/lge-builder-openapi.json
+```
+
+Set bearer token:
+
+```text
+dev-openwebui-builder-token
+```
+
+## Current Contract
+
+The Open WebUI action queues a builder job:
+
+```text
+POST /api/builder/lge/v1/draft
+```
+
+Then it polls:
+
+```text
+GET /api/builder/lge/v1/jobs/:jobId
+```
+
+After artifact persistence, it acknowledges:
+
+```text
+POST /api/builder/lge/v1/jobs/:jobId/ack
+```
+
+Preview and compare links include a signed read-only token, so they do not require the `clonellm` local login cookie.
